BODYTALK

No I not talking about that crap Kids TV prog that was on a 
couple of years ago and consisted of a complete spastic wearing 
pyjamas doing stupid mimes to a bunch of children (not that I'd 
know anything about it of course, it was Mike who told me all 
about it). No no no, not that at all, I'm talking about a Aussie 
proggy that was on a couple of weeks ago, it was all about 
people, dead people to be more specific. They had loads of 
interviews with people who had a job which was something to do 
with dead people. Also at various points in the prog they had a 
bit telling you what happens to a dead body as it decays. For 
example, did you know that after a few days the skin on the hands 
and head shrink so it looks like the hair and the finger nail 
have continued to grow after death, when infact they haven't. 
They told you how the face goes green and the tongue swells up so 
it sticks out of the persons mouth. After about 1 week you can 
easily scratch the person skin away coz it has started to decay. 
Apparently, and this is the bit I found most amazing, after about 
three weeks, there is so much gas inside the body, it with have 
expanded up to three times the size it was when the person died. 
Bloody strange eh? In the interviews one bloke was saying about 
the first time he had to go and pick up a dead guy. He was a drug 
addict and had been dead for a few weeks. By then he was covered 
from head to toe in maggots, and all other sorts of creepy 
crawlies. Anyway the other guy got the blokes feet and he had to 
pick up the head. As he did this the head fell off and all the 
maggots went all over him!!!!!! Another bloke was saying about 
how they discovered a dead body which was about 8-9 weeks old. By 
this time a body is mainly slush, and so they had to get a broom 
and sweep what was left of the body into some plastic bags (so 
they could be examined later). 
   Another thing that was talked about was suicide. One guy had 
got a gun under his chin and blown his own brains out. When the 
police came they had to get buckets and scrap parts of the guys 
brain off the walls with their hands!!! There were bits off the 
bloke everywhere, especially on the ceiling. It all had to be 
scraped of and sent to forensic, don't know why really, I mean it's 
pretty obvious how he died ain't it? When they went into the room 
and found a guy lying on the floor with no head, carrying a shot 
gun, with bits of skull, brain etc. everwhere, they're not going to 
think he did it with poison are they?
   This prog was on channel 4, watch out for the repeat!

